'''Sheldon J. Plankton Jr.''',  or simply '''Plankton''', is a fictional character in the [[Nickelodeon]] animated television series ''[[SpongeBob SquarePants]]''. He is voiced by [[Mr. Lawrence]] and first appeared in the episode "[[SpongeBob SquarePants (season 1)#Plankton!|Plankton!]]" on July 31, 1999. Plankton was created and designed by [[Stephen Hillenburg]]. The character is also in video games and other [[List of SpongeBob SquarePants merchandise|merchandise]] based on the series. Mostly, he has been featured on countless toys, games, plushies, and other popular toys and games.

==Role in ''SpongeBob SquarePants''==
Plankton is the [[archenemy|arch-nemesis]], but former best friend, of [[Mr. Krabs]].<ref name="Friends">{{cite episode|title=Friend or Foe|series=SpongeBob SquarePants|season=5|number=81|channel=Nickelodeon|airdate=April 13, 2007|credits=Writers: Casey Alexander, Zeus Cervas, Mike Mitchell, [[Steven Banks]], [[Tim Hill]]}}</ref> He operates a struggling restaurant called the [[Chum Bucket]].<ref>{{cite episode|title=Plankton!|series=SpongeBob SquarePants|season=1|number=3b|channel=Nickelodeon|airdate=July 31, 1999|credits=Writers: Ennio Torresan, Jr., [[Erik Wiese]], [[Mr. Lawrence]]}}</ref>

Plankton operates the Chum Bucket, located directly across the street from the [[Krusty Krab]].<ref>{{cite episode|title=Komputer Overload|series=SpongeBob SquarePants|season=6|number=118b|channel=Nickelodeon|airdate=March 19, 2009|credits=Writers: [[Aaron Springer]], Richard Pursel}}</ref> The restaurant primarily sells [[chumming|chum]], considered mostly inedible by the residents of Bikini Bottom, and as a result his restaurant is a total commercial failure. His primary goal in the series is to steal the Krabby Patty secret formula and put [[Mr. Krabs]] out of business. Plankton succeeds at stealing the recipe in the [[The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie|movie]], but his goal of world domination is thwarted by SpongeBob and Patrick. It was revealed that Mr. Krabs and Plankton were once best friends, but a dispute over the Krabby Patty recipe ended their friendship.<ref name="Friends"/>

Plankton has a large extended family, containing more than 10,000 members of different forms of plankton, most of whom resemble [[hillbilly|hillbillies]].<ref>{{cite episode|title=Plankton's Army|series=SpongeBob SquarePants|season=3|number=58b|channel=Nickelodeon|airdate=January 19, 2004|credits=Writers: [[Jay Lender]], [[Sam Henderson]], [[Merriwether Williams]]}}</ref>

==Karen==
[[File:KarenW.I.F.E.jpeg|thumb|left|Karen, Plankton's W.I.F.E.]]
Plankton is married to a super computer named Karen. She is his W.I.F.E. (both as an acronym for "Wired Integrated Female Electroencephalograph" and in the sense of a female spouse).<ref>{{cite episode|title=Enemy In-Law|series=SpongeBob SquarePants|season=4|number=67a|channel=Nickelodeon|airdate=October 14, 2005|credits=Writers: [[Tom King (writer)|Tom King]], [[Luke Brookshier]], [[Tim Hill]]}}</ref> She appears to have her own sentient mind and enjoys putting him down, though it's shown that they love each other. She sometimes gets fed up with his antics and forbids him from returning home.<ref>{{cite episode|title=Krabby Road|series=SpongeBob SquarePants|season=6|number=101b|channel=Nickelodeon|airdate=March 3, 2008|credits=Writers: [[Luke Brookshier]], Nate Cash, Eric Shaw}}</ref> She tends to give Plankton most of his ideas to steal the Krabby Patty, but he usually takes them as his own idea.<ref>{{cite episode|title=Chum Caverns|series=SpongeBob SquarePants|season=6|number=125b|channel=Nickelodeon|airdate=July 18, 2009|credits=Writers: Casey Alexander, Zeus Cervas, Richard Pursel}}</ref>

==Merchandising==
Plankton has been featured in various merchandises such as plush toys. In 2006, [[Ty Inc.]]'s [[Beanie Babies]] introduced a plush toy based on the character as part of the ''SpongeBob SquarePants'' series.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ty Spongebob Squarepants Beanie Baby Sheldon J. Plankton|url=http://www.amazon.com/Ty-Spongebob-Squarepants-Sheldon-Plankton/dp/B000VOCCOC|publisher=Amazon.com|accessdate=2 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sheldon J. Plankton|url=http://store.ty.com/newtys/tyshop_items_preview.cfm?ITEM_NO=40664|publisher=Ty Inc.|accessdate=2 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=TY Beanie Baby - SHELDON J PLANKTON (SpongeBob Squarepants) (9 inch)|url=http://www.bbtoystore.com/store/BB_sheldonjplankton.html|publisher=BB Toy Store|accessdate=2 May 2013}}</ref>
